1
00:00:39,140 --> 00:00:40,670
(All characters, places,
and organizations are fictional.)

2
00:00:40,670 --> 00:00:41,970
(Children were filmed
under production guidelines.)

3
00:01:28,690 --> 00:01:30,520
(Episode 3)

4
00:01:42,900 --> 00:01:43,900
Who...

5
00:01:45,070 --> 00:01:47,170
am I? What's your name?

6
00:01:57,320 --> 00:01:58,520
A mirror.

7
00:02:01,520 --> 00:02:04,420
It hurts...

8
00:02:15,940 --> 00:02:16,940
What are you doing?

9
00:02:22,340 --> 00:02:23,340
You're beautiful.

10
00:02:31,550 --> 00:02:32,790
I'll make sure you never get old.

11
00:02:34,720 --> 00:02:37,560
- You'd hate to get wrinkles?
- Wrinkles of the heart.

12
00:02:39,230 --> 00:02:40,760
I don't care about wrinkles on your face.

13
00:03:28,440 --> 00:03:29,440
Tell me.

14
00:03:30,440 --> 00:03:31,440
Your name.

15
00:03:36,450 --> 00:03:37,950
What am I supposed to say?

16
00:03:42,150 --> 00:03:45,560
It hurts...

17
00:03:47,030 --> 00:03:48,030
Does it hurt?

18
00:03:53,300 --> 00:03:54,700
You...

19
00:03:55,500 --> 00:03:56,800
want to...

20
00:03:57,640 --> 00:03:58,770
die?

21
00:04:04,310 --> 00:04:05,580
Don't cry.

22
00:04:09,180 --> 00:04:11,050
You succeeded,
and that's all that matters.

23
00:04:12,050 --> 00:04:13,050
You did it.

24
00:04:14,120 --> 00:04:15,350
You worked so hard.

25
00:05:02,100 --> 00:05:03,200
Goodbye.

26
00:05:21,020 --> 00:05:22,120
This is how I live.

27
00:05:28,560 --> 00:05:30,260
I should've brought some fruit.

28
00:05:32,430 --> 00:05:34,800
- I have milk.
- How's Momo?

29
00:05:36,100 --> 00:05:37,670
- I don't know.
- You don't know?

30
00:05:41,070 --> 00:05:43,110
I'm sure she's recovering well.

31
00:05:43,710 --> 00:05:45,410
James said he hasn't heard
anything either.

32
00:05:45,850 --> 00:05:46,850
It's weird, isn't it?

33
00:05:47,110 --> 00:05:48,910
- Why don't you text her?
- You think I haven't?

34
00:05:51,320 --> 00:05:52,490
But you can go see her.

35
00:05:52,550 --> 00:05:55,320
What? How can I just show up
when she hasn't asked me to?

36
00:05:55,960 --> 00:05:59,330
- She's at Dr. Shin's getting treated.
- For seven months?

37
00:06:00,730 --> 00:06:02,560
Then just how serious is it?

38
00:06:04,300 --> 00:06:06,800
Was she completely unconscious
at the time of the accident?

39
00:06:08,300 --> 00:06:11,870
No one at her agency is talking.
They just say she's recovering.

40
00:06:13,710 --> 00:06:14,940
Is that why you're here?

41
00:06:18,910 --> 00:06:21,850
If her condition were bad,
Director Shin would've fallen apart.

42
00:06:22,180 --> 00:06:25,890
Ms. Hyun also had a couple of fittings
and seemed perfectly normal.

43
00:06:30,590 --> 00:06:31,590
Are you leaving?

44
00:06:39,470 --> 00:06:40,470
Hey.

45
00:06:42,440 --> 00:06:43,800
Don't you have anything to say to me?

46
00:06:46,610 --> 00:06:47,610
About what?

47
00:06:48,710 --> 00:06:49,710
You don't know?

48
00:06:52,710 --> 00:06:54,110
It's just that...

49
00:06:54,950 --> 00:06:58,620
I was hurt because I felt like
you started pulling away from me.

50
00:06:59,690 --> 00:07:00,850
You were hurt?

51
00:07:01,120 --> 00:07:02,120
Yes.

52
00:08:28,010 --> 00:08:31,310
For dinner, I want French Toast
and a Caprese Salad.

53
00:08:32,980 --> 00:08:33,980
Okay?

54
00:08:36,880 --> 00:08:39,690
Caprese Salad.

55
00:08:40,350 --> 00:08:42,290
French Toast.

56
00:08:55,830 --> 00:08:57,740
Get lost...

57
00:09:00,470 --> 00:09:01,470
Get lost.

58
00:09:06,280 --> 00:09:07,480
Get lost.

59
00:09:10,650 --> 00:09:13,190
Is Director Shin still coming
on Wednesday as planned?

60
00:09:40,710 --> 00:09:42,250
There are barely any wrinkles.

61
00:09:43,150 --> 00:09:44,480
I'll look great as long as I dress well.

62
00:09:47,520 --> 00:09:48,520
There.

63
00:09:55,790 --> 00:09:57,230
No.

64
00:10:01,130 --> 00:10:04,040
Excellent. Even I have to admit, I look...

65
00:10:04,400 --> 00:10:06,740
mid-thirties?

66
00:10:08,410 --> 00:10:10,280
When is your birthday, Mr. Ha?

67
00:10:10,680 --> 00:10:13,410
I asked Manager Yoon,
but she wouldn't tell me.

68
00:10:13,580 --> 00:10:17,120
I don't take cakes from my employees.
That's too much sugar.

69
00:10:17,180 --> 00:10:19,320
But still, for us...

70
00:10:22,890 --> 00:10:24,460
Jin Ju, do you drink?

71
00:10:24,890 --> 00:10:26,090
A little.

72
00:10:27,390 --> 00:10:28,890
Should we do the wine pairing?
It's been a while.

73
00:10:30,430 --> 00:10:32,900
Natasha's airport look was great today.

74
00:10:33,470 --> 00:10:35,170
I learned from the best.

75
00:10:35,430 --> 00:10:38,700
I can't take all the credit.
You have to have a natural gift for it.

76
00:10:39,770 --> 00:10:43,110
Should I call you Mr. Ha?
Or do you prefer "Sir?"

77
00:10:43,180 --> 00:10:44,540
Call me whatever you want.

78
00:10:45,240 --> 00:10:48,480
To be honest,
neither of those really suit you.

79
00:10:48,850 --> 00:10:50,950
Then what, you want to call me honey?

80
00:10:51,350 --> 00:10:53,990
- You're like a celebrity.
- I'll take that as a compliment.

81
00:10:54,190 --> 00:10:56,190
Of course. I mean it.

82
00:10:59,660 --> 00:11:01,330
This is so delicious.

83
00:11:04,430 --> 00:11:06,330
This is so delicious, Yong Joong.

84
00:11:10,940 --> 00:11:12,470
They have good pairings here.

85
00:11:13,170 --> 00:11:15,370
Is that birthday on your ID your real one?

86
00:11:18,780 --> 00:11:19,780
You don't know?

87
00:11:22,480 --> 00:11:23,480
No.

88
00:11:23,950 --> 00:11:26,550
- What about Reporter Geum Ba Ra?
- It's the same for Ba Ra.

89
00:11:27,390 --> 00:11:29,720
We even entered the orphanage
on the same day.

90
00:11:31,720 --> 00:11:32,730
Really?

91
00:11:33,890 --> 00:11:36,060
You'll just have to find
yourselves good husbands.

92
00:11:37,460 --> 00:11:40,470
- You think that's possible?
- Where there's a will, there's a way.

93
00:11:41,030 --> 00:11:43,600
They say the deity grants at least one
of your most earnest wishes.

94
00:11:43,970 --> 00:11:45,970
Then why are you still single?

95
00:11:46,770 --> 00:11:48,270
Because I was too busy
taking care of my young brother.

96
00:11:48,470 --> 00:11:51,910
Mr. Ha Yong Joong.
He's ridiculously handsome.

97
00:11:53,710 --> 00:11:55,910
Though he's not quite as handsome
as Director Shin Ju Shin.

98
00:11:56,220 --> 00:11:57,850
You clearly don't have an eye for men.

99
00:11:58,480 --> 00:12:01,220
Whether it's looks or anything else,
Yong Joong is way better.

100
00:12:01,620 --> 00:12:04,260
To each their own, I guess.

101
00:12:05,160 --> 00:12:09,700
But Mr. Ha didn't get far academically,
did he?

102
00:12:10,100 --> 00:12:13,270
What does a formal education matter?
It's his character that's important.

103
00:12:13,470 --> 00:12:16,840
Besides, Yong Joong is smarter
than people with PhDs.

104
00:12:16,840 --> 00:12:18,440
He reads a lot.

105
00:12:20,240 --> 00:12:21,640
It's so tender.

106
00:12:22,540 --> 00:12:23,710
I'll take you out more often.

107
00:12:25,210 --> 00:12:27,450
Is Reporter Geum Ba Ra seeing anyone?

108
00:12:28,480 --> 00:12:30,620
- I have no idea.
- How could you not know?

109
00:12:30,680 --> 00:12:32,380
You said you're practically sisters.

110
00:12:32,990 --> 00:12:34,620
I get the feeling
she's not interested in marriage.

111
00:12:35,350 --> 00:12:37,360
The ones who say they're not interested
in marriage are always the first to marry.

112
00:12:39,460 --> 00:12:41,030
What's Ba Ra's ideal type?

113
00:12:42,490 --> 00:12:44,060
Are you thinking of
setting her up with someone?

114
00:12:46,770 --> 00:12:48,300
You're not thinking of Mr. Ha, are you?

115
00:12:48,570 --> 00:12:50,070
Of course not.

116
00:12:52,500 --> 00:12:54,070
Get lost.

117
00:12:57,310 --> 00:12:59,210
I can't stand the sight of you.

118
00:13:02,250 --> 00:13:04,450
I said, get lost!

119
00:13:06,590 --> 00:13:08,450
Who the heck are you?

120
00:13:09,120 --> 00:13:12,160
Momo, come on. Let Mommy get some sleep.

121
00:13:13,630 --> 00:13:16,430
You're dead meat.

122
00:13:45,060 --> 00:13:46,360
Coffee, and make it weak.

123
00:13:55,330 --> 00:13:56,400
(Post)

124
00:13:59,400 --> 00:14:00,410
What's this?

125
00:14:00,740 --> 00:14:03,340
She's pretty, right?
I thought she might be your type.

126
00:14:04,340 --> 00:14:05,940
(Post)

127
00:14:06,610 --> 00:14:07,850
Looks like she's had work done.

128
00:14:08,910 --> 00:14:13,090
- Nearly everyone gets work done now.
- But you haven't. You're all natural.

129
00:14:14,120 --> 00:14:16,620
- That's because I'm broke.
- You want some?

130
00:14:18,020 --> 00:14:19,590
No, you're perfect just the way you are.

131
00:14:19,890 --> 00:14:21,090
It's not because
I won't give you the money.

132
00:14:23,030 --> 00:14:25,400
"Perfect..."
Is that the right word for a face?

133
00:14:26,000 --> 00:14:27,770
It's more than just being pretty.

134
00:14:28,700 --> 00:14:29,900
Only in your eyes.

135
00:14:31,900 --> 00:14:32,940
She said she's interested in me?

136
00:14:34,870 --> 00:14:38,940
- Yes.
- A PhD likes a middle school dropout?

137
00:14:40,650 --> 00:14:42,610
A high school dropout, to be exact.

138
00:14:42,980 --> 00:14:45,450
- Just meet her once.
- Do you think we'd be a good match?

139
00:14:46,450 --> 00:14:47,450
Yes.

140
00:14:48,550 --> 00:14:51,060
Personality-wise? Our backgrounds?

141
00:14:52,290 --> 00:14:55,090
- She asked me to set you two up.
- I was just asking.

142
00:14:55,160 --> 00:14:56,500
No, you weren't.

143
00:14:57,730 --> 00:14:59,000
You're going to get married, right?

144
00:14:59,670 --> 00:15:01,530
Yes, of course I am.

145
00:15:04,770 --> 00:15:07,070
She comes from a good family,
and she has a great personality.

146
00:15:07,470 --> 00:15:09,140
Plus, she has that foxy look guys go for.

147
00:15:11,810 --> 00:15:13,180
What kind of look do you have, Ba Ra?

148
00:15:18,320 --> 00:15:20,120
I'm clueless
when it comes to women's looks.

149
00:15:21,750 --> 00:15:23,660
Is gaming all you know about?

150
00:15:24,290 --> 00:15:25,320
Pretty much.

151
00:15:28,590 --> 00:15:31,860
Of all the men I know,
aside from our Advisor,

152
00:15:31,930 --> 00:15:33,830
no one is as savvy as you.

153
00:15:33,830 --> 00:15:36,770
You're filled with mature knowledge.

154
00:15:37,970 --> 00:15:39,540
I'll take that as the highest compliment.

155
00:15:39,910 --> 00:15:40,940
It's true.

156
00:15:42,040 --> 00:15:43,440
So when knowledge matures,

157
00:15:43,980 --> 00:15:45,010
does it become wisdom?

158
00:15:47,480 --> 00:15:51,380
You may be half-joking with me,
but I only ever mean what I say.

159
00:15:51,750 --> 00:15:53,290
I don't joke around with just anyone.

160
00:15:57,620 --> 00:15:59,960
How about the Sky Hotel Lounge?

161
00:16:02,830 --> 00:16:03,830
Forget it.

162
00:16:06,670 --> 00:16:09,000
Is the Sky Hotel Lounge okay?

163
00:16:12,040 --> 00:16:13,670
So, is she ready to get married
as early as next month?

164
00:16:17,010 --> 00:16:18,410
That's up to you.

165
00:16:21,310 --> 00:16:22,710
How many cups of coffee
is that for you today?

166
00:16:23,920 --> 00:16:24,920
Four?

167
00:16:25,180 --> 00:16:26,180
That's enough.

168
00:16:27,550 --> 00:16:30,960
Drink something healthy and nutritious.
At least when you're with me.

169
00:16:32,620 --> 00:16:34,360
If this goes well, how about some Chalet?

170
00:16:35,290 --> 00:16:36,430
Is "Eruchal" the thing these days?

171
00:16:37,030 --> 00:16:39,130
I'll deck you out from head to toe.

172
00:16:39,660 --> 00:16:42,900
Clothes by Chalet, shoes by Rugati,
a bag by Evua.

173
00:16:45,700 --> 00:16:46,940
Or an all-Chalet look?

174
00:16:47,470 --> 00:16:49,170
I don't want you to call me
anything different.

175
00:16:50,910 --> 00:16:52,310
Even when we get older,

176
00:16:52,740 --> 00:16:54,480
can't you just keep calling me
what you always have?

177
00:16:55,510 --> 00:16:57,180
I'll take that over all
the designer gifts.

178
00:16:59,350 --> 00:17:00,490
A long time ago,

179
00:17:01,820 --> 00:17:03,520
the first time we met,
in front of the supermarket.

180
00:17:04,620 --> 00:17:05,620
You mean, "Hey, kiddo?"

181
00:17:11,060 --> 00:17:12,660
You're the only person...

182
00:17:14,500 --> 00:17:16,100
who called me that way,

183
00:17:16,800 --> 00:17:17,870
as far as I can remember.

184
00:17:34,450 --> 00:17:35,490
Yong Joong.

185
00:17:39,590 --> 00:17:40,630
We...

186
00:17:41,460 --> 00:17:42,960
seem to really click.

187
00:17:45,560 --> 00:17:46,670
Am I sexy, too?

188
00:17:50,570 --> 00:17:52,570
Turns out, honesty can be sexy.

189
00:17:55,870 --> 00:17:57,410
And you are being
seriously sexy right now.

190
00:18:00,280 --> 00:18:01,410
(James)

191
00:18:05,420 --> 00:18:07,220
- Hey, James.
- Are you out?

192
00:18:07,290 --> 00:18:09,990
Yeah, at a local café with Ba Ra.
You're on speakerphone.

193
00:18:10,590 --> 00:18:11,790
Hey, Reporter Geum.

194
00:18:12,820 --> 00:18:16,030
- Hello.
- So what did my brother get you?

195
00:18:16,360 --> 00:18:17,600
What did he buy you?

196
00:18:17,700 --> 00:18:21,970
Not even a teddy bear this time.
He just said Korean stuff is better.

197
00:18:22,130 --> 00:18:26,470
- I'll get her a bag tomorrow. I'm broke.
- Make sure you get it.

198
00:18:27,140 --> 00:18:30,210
By the way, Reporter Geum,
have you spoken with Momo recently?

199
00:18:30,840 --> 00:18:34,350
- No.
- Is it possible she hasn't woken up yet?

200
00:18:34,610 --> 00:18:36,880
- Why?
- You didn't hear from Reporter Geum?

201
00:18:37,320 --> 00:18:41,520
Momo supposedly passed out scuba diving,
but now she's completely off the radar.

202
00:19:15,590 --> 00:19:16,590
You startled me.

203
00:19:24,230 --> 00:19:26,970
- Are you on a diet?
- I ate way too much yesterday.

204
00:19:32,440 --> 00:19:33,470
It's weird saying this, but...

205
00:19:34,240 --> 00:19:38,210
- Go on.
- I think you would've made a great woman.

206
00:19:38,980 --> 00:19:42,010
- A compliment on my cooking or an insult?
- A compliment.

207
00:19:42,510 --> 00:19:44,250
But there are way too many side dishes.

208
00:19:47,390 --> 00:19:49,390
I don't eat like this when I'm by myself.

209
00:19:49,450 --> 00:19:52,420
You're really getting old.
You used to stuff your face late at night,

210
00:19:52,490 --> 00:19:55,430
and still grill meat at dawn.
Now that you're pushing 50...

211
00:19:58,530 --> 00:20:01,670
I'm a light sleeper.
Why didn't I hear your car pull up?

212
00:20:01,830 --> 00:20:04,470
Because you're old.
Your hearing is the next thing to go.

213
00:20:04,540 --> 00:20:07,640
- Your eyes are already going, too.
- You think you'll stay young forever?

214
00:20:07,740 --> 00:20:10,340
- No.
- You're really asking for it.

215
00:20:10,980 --> 00:20:12,910
I took a cab because I drank.

216
00:20:18,150 --> 00:20:19,920
Is something wrong at the company?

217
00:20:23,190 --> 00:20:24,620
Maybe something's wrong with Momo.

218
00:20:25,790 --> 00:20:27,460
Is that what's bothering you?

219
00:20:28,660 --> 00:20:30,400
Yesterday,
I just felt like having a drink.

220
00:20:31,660 --> 00:20:36,470
Forget Momo and focus on your own life.
I'm dying to hold a niece or nephew.

221
00:20:37,170 --> 00:20:38,500
That's my wish, too.

222
00:20:39,700 --> 00:20:41,470
Is it that hard for you to move on?

223
00:20:42,010 --> 00:20:43,170
Why wouldn't I be able to?

224
00:20:45,210 --> 00:20:46,980
It's just that I'm concerned, that's all.

225
00:20:47,610 --> 00:20:50,550
Why would you be concerned?
She's your best friend's fiancee.

226
00:20:50,850 --> 00:20:52,420
I wouldn't be
if they were happily married.

227
00:20:53,220 --> 00:20:54,820
You think I've only known Ju Shin
for two years?

228
00:20:57,590 --> 00:20:59,290
And it feels like he's hiding something.

229
00:21:02,660 --> 00:21:05,200
I looked into it,
and her decompression sickness is severe.

230
00:21:05,360 --> 00:21:07,600
You can bet Director Shin is taking
the best possible care of her.

231
00:21:09,370 --> 00:21:11,540
Here, take a container of this kimchi
to Ba Ra.

232
00:21:12,000 --> 00:21:13,140
I don't know her address.

233
00:21:14,570 --> 00:21:15,840
You don't know her address?

234
00:21:34,460 --> 00:21:36,160
Burn it. I'm not taking it.

235
00:21:41,670 --> 00:21:43,700
(Nua General Hospital)

236
00:22:05,520 --> 00:22:07,860
Momo, get a grip.

237
00:22:08,460 --> 00:22:09,660
Walk like you're okay.

238
00:22:24,040 --> 00:22:25,110
(Republic of Korea passport)

239
00:22:43,090 --> 00:22:44,900
Director Shin, you know Geum Ba Ra, right?

240
00:22:45,800 --> 00:22:46,870
Yes.

241
00:22:46,970 --> 00:22:49,970
I think Ba Ra is digging around
for information on Momo.

242
00:22:50,100 --> 00:22:52,170
It looks like she even met with
the scuba instructor.

243
00:22:55,470 --> 00:22:58,840
I'm not writing an article, I promise.
You know me better than that, Manager Oh.

244
00:22:59,140 --> 00:23:01,150
CEO Hyun said she's doing perfectly fine.

245
00:23:01,350 --> 00:23:02,710
Have you seen her since the accident?

246
00:23:03,280 --> 00:23:04,950
- I haven't.
- Does that make sense?

247
00:23:05,020 --> 00:23:06,890
She told me not to worry, so...

248
00:23:08,420 --> 00:23:11,420
- If you meet with CEO Hyun...
- I've already texted her,

249
00:23:12,260 --> 00:23:13,390
but I got no reply.

250
00:23:22,670 --> 00:23:23,670
So?

251
00:23:26,500 --> 00:23:30,710
I just thought you should know
since it's about Momo.

252
00:23:37,120 --> 00:23:40,190
Doesn't it seem strange to you too?
With your reporter's intuition.

253
00:23:46,520 --> 00:23:47,530
Like you say,

254
00:23:48,990 --> 00:23:50,630
what if Momo is in some kind of...

255
00:23:51,600 --> 00:23:53,200
worst-case scenario,

256
00:23:55,670 --> 00:23:56,900
what are you going to do then?

257
00:24:01,510 --> 00:24:02,640
When it comes to the heart...

258
00:24:05,210 --> 00:24:07,010
Shin Ju Shin has a cold side.

259
00:24:07,580 --> 00:24:09,210
To put it nicely, he's just rational.

260
00:24:10,850 --> 00:24:12,220
And it's not like they're married.

261
00:24:13,850 --> 00:24:16,390
In that situation, I wonder how long
he can keep looking after her.

262
00:24:17,790 --> 00:24:20,690
He's bound to get worn out.
And it's not like he has a low-stress job.

263
00:24:23,230 --> 00:24:24,600
And you wouldn't get worn out?

264
00:24:32,370 --> 00:24:33,610
Slow down.

265
00:24:43,550 --> 00:24:45,020
You've never really been in love,
have you?

266
00:24:48,190 --> 00:24:49,720
And for you, that's Momo?

267
00:24:54,490 --> 00:24:55,990
What's so great about her, anyway?

268
00:24:57,930 --> 00:24:59,030
Is it because she's a celebrity?

269
00:25:00,470 --> 00:25:02,570
Lee Ye Rim, Hong Mi Jeong,
and Jeong Chun Hee are celebrities, too.

270
00:25:02,730 --> 00:25:04,200
I've met them all at gatherings.

271
00:25:06,870 --> 00:25:07,970
You can't really explain...

272
00:25:09,610 --> 00:25:11,280
a person's feelings, you know?

273
00:25:14,410 --> 00:25:16,850
If the situation is really that serious,

274
00:25:18,320 --> 00:25:20,420
and Director Shin
eventually gives up on her...

275
00:25:23,660 --> 00:25:25,420
are you saying you're going to take
responsibility for her?

276
00:25:27,730 --> 00:25:28,730
For her entire life?

277
00:25:34,930 --> 00:25:36,470
How noble of you.

278
00:25:37,770 --> 00:25:40,270
To Mr. Ha and his undying love.

279
00:25:48,380 --> 00:25:49,980
You're not being yourself today.

280
00:25:50,580 --> 00:25:51,680
You're so cynical.

281
00:25:53,790 --> 00:25:55,250
How well do you even know me?

282
00:25:56,590 --> 00:25:59,290
What is it that I don't know? Tell me.

283
00:26:02,330 --> 00:26:05,860
Other than that I was an abandoned orphan,
you know nothing about me.

284
00:26:06,330 --> 00:26:07,700
You weren't abandoned.

285
00:26:08,600 --> 00:26:11,000
It must have been an impossible situation.
I can tell by looking at you.

286
00:26:12,070 --> 00:26:13,540
I can tell it's in your blood.

287
00:26:14,510 --> 00:26:15,670
You've got good character.

288
00:26:18,440 --> 00:26:19,540
My name...

289
00:26:21,480 --> 00:26:22,580
Who gave you that name?

290
00:26:25,320 --> 00:26:26,780
How would I know?

291
00:26:31,920 --> 00:26:33,160
But I think...

292
00:26:33,760 --> 00:26:35,030
It's just a guess...

293
00:26:38,630 --> 00:26:39,830
I'd rather not say.

294
00:26:46,840 --> 00:26:47,840
Are you mad at me?

295
00:26:50,480 --> 00:26:52,110
I thought you'd understand.

296
00:26:56,480 --> 00:27:00,080
I don't like how you're addressing me.
Don't call me Mr. Ha. It feels impersonal.

297
00:27:00,720 --> 00:27:02,320
It's not like we have that many employees.

298
00:27:03,820 --> 00:27:05,720
You should meet Director Shin,

299
00:27:06,390 --> 00:27:08,830
find a way to see Momo for yourself,

300
00:27:09,660 --> 00:27:11,400
and settle this once and for all.

301
00:27:21,670 --> 00:27:24,580
I have an article to write.
I'll get going.

302
00:27:25,410 --> 00:27:26,410
- Excuse me?
- Yes.

303
00:27:26,480 --> 00:27:27,510
No, go ahead and finish your drink.

304
00:27:39,290 --> 00:27:40,530
(Available)

305
00:29:17,120 --> 00:29:18,260
How's Momo?

306
00:29:20,890 --> 00:29:22,360
I don't want her to see me like this.

307
00:29:26,030 --> 00:29:27,130
She's the same.

308
00:29:33,640 --> 00:29:35,270
Don't let your mind run wild.

309
00:29:36,170 --> 00:29:37,880
I'll wrap this up without any issues.

310
00:29:40,110 --> 00:29:41,250
How are you going to wrap it up?

311
00:29:44,120 --> 00:29:46,120
How did your seminar presentation go?

312
00:29:47,250 --> 00:29:48,250
It was fine.

313
00:29:49,690 --> 00:29:52,590
- I'm sorry. I came empty-handed.
- Don't be silly.

314
00:29:55,530 --> 00:29:56,730
This is all very confusing, isn't it?

315
00:29:57,330 --> 00:29:58,860
You'll get used to it. Eventually.

316
00:30:01,400 --> 00:30:03,500
You should go. You must be tired.

317
00:30:29,030 --> 00:30:30,660
Sometimes when I look in the mirror,

318
00:30:31,360 --> 00:30:34,930
I can't tell if I'm Momo
or if I'm looking at her.

319
00:31:36,560 --> 00:31:41,930
(Yong Joong)

320
00:32:07,060 --> 00:32:08,090
Momo...

321
00:32:11,900 --> 00:32:13,660
How can I live without seeing her?

322
00:32:34,950 --> 00:32:36,550
(Ba Ra)

323
00:32:36,920 --> 00:32:38,460
(Send me your address...)

324
00:32:45,660 --> 00:32:47,370
(Send me your address...)

325
00:32:47,430 --> 00:32:48,430
(Where do you live? Are you asleep?)

326
00:33:10,290 --> 00:33:11,490
(Yong Joong)

327
00:33:11,720 --> 00:33:13,060
Are you still mad, kiddo?

328
00:33:33,740 --> 00:33:34,750
What book is that?

329
00:33:35,350 --> 00:33:37,450
("Mouth Management")

330
00:33:39,950 --> 00:33:40,950
Come on up.

331
00:33:42,450 --> 00:33:46,320
- Is this a bad time?
- I can't eat out. I have surgery later.

332
00:34:00,470 --> 00:34:04,910
We were all in disbelief
when your father passed so suddenly.

333
00:34:04,980 --> 00:34:07,850
- Were you there?
- As the orphanage's representative.

334
00:34:08,780 --> 00:34:10,510
So many people came to pay their respects.

335
00:34:11,880 --> 00:34:15,420
Honestly, my mother's death was harder.
I was just a kid.

336
00:34:17,120 --> 00:34:18,120
Am I making you uncomfortable?

337
00:34:18,760 --> 00:34:21,460
Do you mind if I get this to go?
I usually have late lunch.

338
00:34:21,730 --> 00:34:22,830
This is my first meal of the day.

339
00:34:25,060 --> 00:34:26,760
Are you going around investigating Momo?

340
00:34:27,970 --> 00:34:30,230
- I heard about it.
- From who?

341
00:34:35,840 --> 00:34:38,240
- It's not an investigation. It's...
- For a story?

342
00:34:38,740 --> 00:34:39,840
Or as a concerned friend?

343
00:34:43,750 --> 00:34:45,450
I heard you two were pretty close.

344
00:34:48,920 --> 00:34:52,590
I'm just worried.
I haven't heard from her in so long.

345
00:34:52,890 --> 00:34:55,690
Her phone is still turned off,
and Jin Ju said she had an accident...

346
00:34:55,760 --> 00:34:57,030
It wasn't that serious an accident.

347
00:34:58,400 --> 00:34:59,800
She's out of the country.

348
00:35:00,700 --> 00:35:02,530
She was exhausted,
so I told her to take a break.

349
00:35:05,100 --> 00:35:06,370
She'll be back soon enough.

350
00:35:07,470 --> 00:35:09,210
About me and Momo dating...

351
00:35:10,440 --> 00:35:11,580
Did you hear it from Kim Jin Ju?

352
00:35:13,710 --> 00:35:17,280
I can't reveal my sources.
It wasn't Jin Ju.

353
00:35:17,350 --> 00:35:21,390
We're both too busy to see each other.
We just run into each other at gatherings.

354
00:35:21,450 --> 00:35:22,950
And even that was only once in a while.

355
00:35:23,020 --> 00:35:25,320
You know my father was very proud of you,
don't you?

356
00:35:29,090 --> 00:35:30,460
Running the foundation...

357
00:35:31,260 --> 00:35:32,560
He found it so worthwhile.

358
00:35:35,930 --> 00:35:38,070
If you ever need help with anything,
let me know.

359
00:35:38,740 --> 00:35:41,040
- I don't.
- You never know.

360
00:35:41,670 --> 00:35:42,840
Don't be so sure.

361
00:35:44,840 --> 00:35:47,610
By the way,
I saw you interviewed Ha Yong Joong.

362
00:35:48,050 --> 00:35:49,280
He's been a friend of mine
since we were kids.

363
00:35:50,210 --> 00:35:52,920
He also played the double bass
at the appreciation gala.

364
00:35:52,980 --> 00:35:54,690
Why did you leave so early that night?

365
00:35:55,690 --> 00:35:57,890
I was running a little late
because I had an emergency surgery,

366
00:35:59,060 --> 00:36:00,060
and I saw you were leaving.

367
00:36:01,130 --> 00:36:02,730
I remember because of your ivory coat.

368
00:36:03,560 --> 00:36:05,760
My mother used to wear an ivory coat
a lot.

369
00:36:08,830 --> 00:36:10,670
Please tell Momo I said hi.

370
00:36:15,540 --> 00:36:16,770
I'll take it to go.

371
00:36:21,610 --> 00:36:24,250
Pack it for her to go. The sandwiches.

372
00:36:32,790 --> 00:36:35,790
I can't relay the message.
You should tell her in person.

373
00:36:43,600 --> 00:36:44,600
Hello?

374
00:36:45,500 --> 00:36:48,070
- Yes?
- Where've you been? Haven't you seen it?

375
00:36:48,140 --> 00:36:50,740
- The article on Momo's engagement.
- Where did it run?

376
00:36:51,480 --> 00:36:52,510
Got it.

377
00:36:55,750 --> 00:36:57,780
The inevitable has happened, Momo.

378
00:36:58,150 --> 00:36:59,920
Did you already know about this, sir?

379
00:37:05,320 --> 00:37:06,890
("Exclusive, Momo's Secret Engagement!")

380
00:37:06,890 --> 00:37:08,030
("Fiance is Director Shin Ju Shin
of Nua Medical")

381
00:37:16,230 --> 00:37:18,300
("Exclusive, Momo's Secret Engagement!")

382
00:37:18,300 --> 00:37:19,670
(Two families have met.
Yet, there is no official announcement.)

383
00:37:22,940 --> 00:37:24,580
(Surprised by his handsome looks,
belying his director title...)

384
00:37:24,640 --> 00:37:25,640
(Innocent looks that belie his title...)

385
00:37:25,710 --> 00:37:27,440
(and even more surprised
by his fresh-faced youth)

386
00:37:27,510 --> 00:37:30,710
(We interviewed Director Shin and heard
the full story of their romance.)

387
00:37:35,190 --> 00:37:36,720
- Is this for real?
- We need to publish by eight o'clock.

388
00:37:37,590 --> 00:37:39,760
- Hey, over there.
- This is it.

389
00:37:45,860 --> 00:37:48,200
("Exclusive Interview with Momo's Fiance,
Director Shin Ju Shin")

390
00:37:48,870 --> 00:37:51,570
I just met with Director Shin Ju Shin
and posted the interview.

391
00:37:51,940 --> 00:37:52,940
You interviewed him?

392
00:37:53,240 --> 00:37:55,010
- Yes.
- When?

393
00:37:55,070 --> 00:37:58,580
- I was with him when you called earlier.
- You should've told me then!

394
00:37:59,180 --> 00:38:00,180
I knew you'd pull through.

395
00:38:11,190 --> 00:38:12,190
Yes?

396
00:38:12,920 --> 00:38:14,630
I just met with Director Shin Ju Shin.

397
00:38:15,260 --> 00:38:17,930
He said Momo's fine
and that she's gone abroad to rest.

398
00:38:19,630 --> 00:38:20,630
That's a relief.

399
00:38:23,670 --> 00:38:24,740
Did you see the article?

400
00:38:26,040 --> 00:38:27,040
Yes.

401
00:38:30,410 --> 00:38:34,140
Can you toss me a decent engagement photo?
You must've taken some, right?

402
00:38:34,450 --> 00:38:35,710
A really nice one of the two of them.

403
00:38:37,350 --> 00:38:38,450
Ju Shin would kill me.

404
00:38:38,820 --> 00:38:40,990
His picture's already out there
and the story went viral.

405
00:38:41,820 --> 00:38:43,650
Do you have any idea
how much my boss chewed me out?

406
00:38:44,150 --> 00:38:46,020
All because I was trying to be loyal
and keep it a secret...

407
00:38:49,090 --> 00:38:51,030
I won't reveal my source, of course.

408
00:38:51,530 --> 00:38:54,160
People will just assume
it was leaked by the wedding studio.

409
00:38:54,630 --> 00:38:56,730
- If I can't make up for this...
- All right, fine.

410
00:38:58,770 --> 00:38:59,800
What's with the sudden change of heart?

411
00:39:00,600 --> 00:39:01,940
You've been ignoring
all my calls and texts.

412
00:39:04,980 --> 00:39:06,040
It's not a change of heart.

413
00:39:07,210 --> 00:39:08,210
Then what is it?

414
00:39:09,950 --> 00:39:10,950
I'm sorry.

415
00:39:11,450 --> 00:39:12,780
I'll be more respectful from now on.

416
00:39:15,220 --> 00:39:17,420
- Director Shin Ju Shin!
- Just give us one comment!

417
00:39:17,490 --> 00:39:19,090
- I have an interview with Mr. Shin!
- He has patients to see.

418
00:39:19,160 --> 00:39:22,060
- We're reporting from Momo's house.
- Please just open the door!

419
00:39:22,160 --> 00:39:23,530
- We're from CBS News!
- Come on, please open the door!

420
00:39:23,590 --> 00:39:25,730
- Please, just open the door!
- Just open up!

421
00:39:25,800 --> 00:39:26,800
This will only take a moment!

422
00:39:40,980 --> 00:39:41,980
What are you doing?

423
00:39:44,150 --> 00:39:45,150
Go back inside.

424
00:39:48,750 --> 00:39:49,750
Who am I?

425
00:39:53,390 --> 00:39:54,660
I...

426
00:39:56,090 --> 00:39:58,500
The one you're referring to...
Who is that?

427
00:40:04,640 --> 00:40:05,970
Don't you miss me?

428
00:40:07,170 --> 00:40:08,310
You don't remember me?

429
00:40:11,580 --> 00:40:12,740
I don't know.

430
00:40:17,410 --> 00:40:18,720
Get lost.

431
00:40:19,720 --> 00:40:20,720
You get lost.

432
00:40:23,920 --> 00:40:25,360
You're so dead.

433
00:40:26,220 --> 00:40:27,390
How can you say that to me, your mom?

434
00:40:29,930 --> 00:40:31,060
(Surgery Center)

435
00:40:31,760 --> 00:40:32,760
What am I going to do?

436
00:40:33,300 --> 00:40:35,500
They won't stop ringing the bell,
so I had to turn off the intercom.

437
00:40:36,130 --> 00:40:37,400
For now, there's no other way...

438
00:40:39,340 --> 00:40:40,340
but to endure it.

439
00:40:40,870 --> 00:40:43,040
So we endure it, and then what?

440
00:40:45,610 --> 00:40:46,610
They broke up?

441
00:40:46,880 --> 00:40:47,910
I'll think about it.

442
00:40:50,380 --> 00:40:51,380
Let me think about it.

443
00:40:53,150 --> 00:40:54,220
I guess you have no other choice.

444
00:40:59,760 --> 00:41:01,120
Then just announce it tomorrow.

445
00:41:01,760 --> 00:41:02,890
I won't have any time for a while.

446
00:41:04,090 --> 00:41:05,430
And that'll just stir up
another huge mess.

447
00:41:05,600 --> 00:41:07,760
If you're so busy, why'd you
even do that interview with Sungwoo Daily?

448
00:41:08,130 --> 00:41:09,130
I didn't give them an interview.

449
00:41:09,830 --> 00:41:10,870
She's a reporter, all right.

450
00:41:12,740 --> 00:41:14,510
I heard she was snooping around
like she was onto something.

451
00:41:14,870 --> 00:41:16,210
So I called her in
and gave her the runaround, but...

452
00:41:16,570 --> 00:41:17,610
And that's what she wrote?

453
00:41:18,110 --> 00:41:19,110
Yes.

454
00:41:20,680 --> 00:41:23,510
Hello. We met before
at the exhibit with Momo.

455
00:41:24,050 --> 00:41:25,280
I'm from the culture desk
at Sungwoo Daily.

456
00:41:27,180 --> 00:41:28,890
I could tell she was something else.

457
00:41:29,990 --> 00:41:31,050
(Sungwoo Daily)

458
00:41:32,520 --> 00:41:34,360
(Director Shin Ju Shin)

459
00:41:39,300 --> 00:41:40,630
(Director Shin Ju Shin)

460
00:41:42,230 --> 00:41:43,230
Yes, Director Shin.

461
00:41:43,870 --> 00:41:45,340
Did I have an interview with you today?

462
00:41:47,200 --> 00:41:48,210
I'm sorry.

463
00:41:48,910 --> 00:41:51,740
I'm in the middle of writing the article.
Can I call you back when I'm done?

464
00:41:52,080 --> 00:41:53,080
Another story about us?

465
00:41:53,680 --> 00:41:55,450
Yes, a follow-up piece.

466
00:41:56,050 --> 00:41:57,050
Geum Ba Ra.

467
00:41:57,450 --> 00:41:58,450
Yes, Director Shin.

468
00:41:59,920 --> 00:42:01,080
You're biting the hand that fed you?

469
00:42:02,250 --> 00:42:04,720
And you, of all people,
are going to take it even further?

470
00:42:05,460 --> 00:42:07,690
- After you read the article...
- Don't write anything else.

471
00:42:10,660 --> 00:42:13,560
Rather than let other outlets
write sensationalist garbage,

472
00:42:14,000 --> 00:42:15,900
it's better to release
a well-written story based on the facts...

473
00:42:15,970 --> 00:42:18,900
and help both of your images.
That is my professional opinion.

474
00:42:19,140 --> 00:42:20,300
And who are you to make that call?

475
00:42:21,200 --> 00:42:23,510
An interview that never happened.
That's what's fiction, an outright lie.

476
00:42:24,140 --> 00:42:25,480
I'll make sure you have nothing
to worry about.

477
00:42:25,540 --> 00:42:27,740
Is that what they taught you
at the Nua Orphanage?

478
00:42:28,210 --> 00:42:29,580
I wasn't taught anything there.

479
00:42:30,010 --> 00:42:33,320
You should have a shred of conscience.
You'll stop at nothing...

480
00:42:33,380 --> 00:42:34,990
I'll call you when I'm finished.

481
00:42:36,250 --> 00:42:37,250
Goodbye.

482
00:42:46,430 --> 00:42:48,030
("Rumors of Momo's Broken Engagement,
Couple Not in Contact")

483
00:42:48,100 --> 00:42:50,030
("Momo's Representative on Rumors:
'No Comment,' A Puzzling Response")

484
00:42:50,100 --> 00:42:51,370
("Scoop:
Momo's Fairytale-like Secret Engagement")

485
00:42:53,140 --> 00:42:54,440
("Scoop:
Momo's Fairytale-like Secret Engagement")

486
00:42:54,870 --> 00:42:56,670
("Momo's Fairytale-like
Secret Engagement")

487
00:42:58,840 --> 00:43:00,640
("Momo's Fairytale-like
Secret Engagement")

488
00:43:00,710 --> 00:43:04,150
(Geum Ba Ra)

489
00:43:08,490 --> 00:43:09,490
Hello?

490
00:43:10,720 --> 00:43:11,720
This is Geum Ba Ra.

491
00:43:12,190 --> 00:43:13,890
Because of this exclusive interview
that never happened,

492
00:43:15,060 --> 00:43:16,560
all the other news outlets
are in an uproar.

493
00:43:17,460 --> 00:43:20,060
May I state my opinion?

494
00:43:22,830 --> 00:43:24,940
At the end of the day,
it's true that you two are engaged.

495
00:43:25,000 --> 00:43:27,040
It's a reporter's calling
to report the truth.

496
00:43:28,640 --> 00:43:30,040
I'm asking why you published
a fabricated story.

497
00:43:31,540 --> 00:43:33,780
What did Momo say?

498
00:43:36,250 --> 00:43:38,020
Just answer my question.

499
00:43:38,650 --> 00:43:40,080
As you said,

500
00:43:40,450 --> 00:43:42,990
When the Chairman treated me to dinner
after I got into college,

501
00:43:43,550 --> 00:43:46,960
he told me I was the face
and the pride of Nua Orphanage.

502
00:43:47,590 --> 00:43:50,130
Everyone at my company knows
I grew up in an orphanage,

503
00:43:50,560 --> 00:43:52,930
so I have to work harder than the others
just so they won't dismiss me.

504
00:43:53,000 --> 00:43:55,030
That's how I survive in this business
without getting crushed.

505
00:43:55,670 --> 00:43:57,170
If I succeed and make a name for myself,

506
00:43:57,970 --> 00:44:00,870
you think you'll never need a favor
from me, Director Shin?

507
00:44:01,740 --> 00:44:03,110
You think I don't have connections
in the media?

508
00:44:04,980 --> 00:44:06,010
I've more than I know what to do with.

509
00:44:06,940 --> 00:44:10,610
I'm sure you do.
But I'm not just a typical connection.

510
00:44:11,380 --> 00:44:13,520
When you get down to it,
you could call me family.

511
00:44:14,080 --> 00:44:15,620
Part of the Nua Foundation family.

512
00:44:18,960 --> 00:44:22,060
Please, just think of it
as giving me a leg up.

513
00:44:23,360 --> 00:44:24,830
You have every right to be upset.

514
00:44:26,430 --> 00:44:27,760
And for that, I apologize.

515
00:44:29,570 --> 00:44:32,540
To be honest,
I knew about your engagement for a while.

516
00:44:34,140 --> 00:44:35,270
You heard it from Kim Jin Ju, didn't you?

517
00:44:36,340 --> 00:44:39,040
I'm on the Culture Desk, so I have sources
at the salons that celebrities frequent.

518
00:44:39,110 --> 00:44:41,680
I get all kinds of intel from them.
It's fast and accurate.

519
00:44:45,250 --> 00:44:46,250
I'll let it slide this time.

520
00:44:46,820 --> 00:44:48,050
Don't you dare stab me in the back again.

521
00:44:49,450 --> 00:44:50,450
I promise.

522
00:44:52,120 --> 00:44:53,490
You owe me one.

523
00:44:55,090 --> 00:44:58,600
I wouldn't be where I am today
without the Chairman and you, Director.

524
00:44:59,260 --> 00:45:01,130
I will be sure to repay everything I owe,
including this.

525
00:45:01,600 --> 00:45:03,600
I don't care if you're a reporter
or the head of a media company,

526
00:45:04,770 --> 00:45:06,140
You do not cross the line with me.

527
00:45:07,870 --> 00:45:09,940
Yes. I'm sorry.

528
00:45:10,610 --> 00:45:11,610
You can go now.

529
00:45:11,980 --> 00:45:12,980
Yes, sir.

530
00:45:53,220 --> 00:45:54,650
Is there anything you want to eat?

531
00:45:59,090 --> 00:46:00,160
Who am I?

532
00:46:24,750 --> 00:46:26,050
(To my dearest Momo,)

533
00:46:26,120 --> 00:46:27,350
My dearest Momo.

534
00:46:28,850 --> 00:46:29,920
If it weren't for you,

535
00:46:31,560 --> 00:46:34,590
I would've left this world
a long time ago.

536
00:46:36,130 --> 00:46:37,630
That I have to leave you like this...

537
00:46:50,110 --> 00:46:51,710
this mother who is leaving you now...

538
00:46:52,480 --> 00:46:54,280
I hope you can understand and forgive me.

539
00:46:56,680 --> 00:46:58,480
I could never let you see,

540
00:46:59,550 --> 00:47:00,820
but at some point,

541
00:47:01,550 --> 00:47:05,920
I find it hard to even breathe.

542
00:47:08,120 --> 00:47:09,290
For no reason at all,

543
00:47:10,330 --> 00:47:11,900
every day was filled with despair...

544
00:47:12,660 --> 00:47:13,960
and sorrow.

545
00:47:15,830 --> 00:47:17,530
I tried to hold on a little longer,

546
00:47:19,200 --> 00:47:21,070
but in place of this weak,
pathetic mother,

547
00:47:23,110 --> 00:47:24,140
you have Director Shin,
someone who cherishes you...

548
00:47:25,380 --> 00:47:27,710
and loves you so dearly.

549
00:47:28,780 --> 00:47:29,950
I can leave now, because I trust him.

550
00:47:32,780 --> 00:47:34,520
Please, let me go without any tears.

551
00:47:37,650 --> 00:47:38,660
I feel deeply sorry...

552
00:47:39,590 --> 00:47:41,860
to Dr. Jung,

553
00:47:42,360 --> 00:47:45,300
who tried everything...

554
00:47:46,130 --> 00:47:47,160
to cure the sickness in my soul.

555
00:47:49,230 --> 00:47:50,670
To my many acquaintances,

556
00:47:52,440 --> 00:47:54,740
I can see all their faces now.

557
00:47:56,940 --> 00:47:59,810
My dear daughter,
don't be foolish like me...

558
00:48:00,210 --> 00:48:02,380
and don't bury yourself in your work.

559
00:48:03,810 --> 00:48:07,780
From now on, learn to enjoy life a little,

560
00:48:09,090 --> 00:48:10,990
and always try to keep your spirits up.

561
00:48:15,490 --> 00:48:20,000
Please, live a long and healthy life.
Live well, for my sake too.

562
00:48:22,370 --> 00:48:25,240
The good deeds I wasn't able to finish...

563
00:48:27,070 --> 00:48:29,070
Do plenty of them with Director Shin.

564
00:48:31,010 --> 00:48:32,710
I don't want to be buried
in the cold, dark ground.

565
00:48:35,310 --> 00:48:36,310
Please have me cremated.

566
00:48:39,280 --> 00:48:41,520
I love you, my daughter.

567
00:48:44,320 --> 00:48:49,760
(Paul Kim)

568
00:48:54,200 --> 00:48:57,130
(Incoming Call)

569
00:49:01,300 --> 00:49:02,310
This is Paul Kim.

570
00:49:02,940 --> 00:49:07,210
Hi, I'm calling about the painting
you sold to CEO James Ha of Lim Company.

571
00:49:08,880 --> 00:49:09,880
Yes.

572
00:49:10,380 --> 00:49:11,850
I'm an acquaintance of CEO Ha's.

573
00:49:12,580 --> 00:49:15,290
I found the mood of that painting
so unique and refreshing.

574
00:49:16,090 --> 00:49:17,920
I assume you have other pieces
at your studio?

575
00:49:19,020 --> 00:49:22,730
- I do.
- I'd like to purchase one. May I stop by?

576
00:49:23,030 --> 00:49:24,830
My studio is on the outskirts of Seoul.

577
00:49:25,130 --> 00:49:27,400
That's fine.
It's only one hour at most with traffic.

578
00:49:27,800 --> 00:49:28,800
Do you have the address?

579
00:49:30,070 --> 00:49:31,170
Could you give it to me?

580
00:49:50,750 --> 00:49:51,820
It's open. Come on in.

581
00:50:11,140 --> 00:50:13,210
Paul Kim?

582
00:50:14,910 --> 00:50:15,910
Yes.

583
00:50:16,750 --> 00:50:18,920
Hello. Sorry I'm a bit late.

584
00:50:20,350 --> 00:50:23,590
The drive up here is just beautiful.

585
00:50:24,620 --> 00:50:25,620
Please, have a seat.

586
00:50:37,200 --> 00:50:39,370
You don't have any of your work
on display?

587
00:50:40,070 --> 00:50:41,070
No, I don't.

588
00:50:41,500 --> 00:50:42,970
They're in my studio
and on the second floor.

589
00:50:45,380 --> 00:50:47,610
- All I have is coffee.
- Coffee is perfect.

590
00:50:48,340 --> 00:50:49,880
No espresso, I presume?

591
00:50:53,120 --> 00:50:54,120
I'm just kidding.

592
00:50:59,360 --> 00:51:01,020
He surely is an artist.

593
00:51:01,860 --> 00:51:03,490
He's middle-aged,
but not an ounce of fat on him.

594
00:51:41,760 --> 00:51:42,770
This is delicious.

595
00:51:43,930 --> 00:51:44,930
It's German coffee.

596
00:51:45,670 --> 00:51:47,700
I heard you were based in Germany.

597
00:51:48,440 --> 00:51:49,440
Yes.

598
00:51:50,640 --> 00:51:53,680
I wasn't sure what to get you,
so I came empty-handed.

599
00:51:58,380 --> 00:51:59,380
You really didn't have to.

600
00:52:00,050 --> 00:52:01,050
There's nothing I need.

601
00:52:01,890 --> 00:52:03,020
I just meant some basic necessities.

602
00:52:05,120 --> 00:52:07,920
He's so stoic, like a Zen monk.

603
00:52:15,500 --> 00:52:16,500
I'm Hyun Ran Hee, by the way.

604
00:52:20,170 --> 00:52:21,870
(CEO Hyun Ran Hee)

605
00:52:24,140 --> 00:52:25,640
He must have heard of me.

606
00:52:28,410 --> 00:52:29,910
Do you do photography as well?

607
00:52:31,550 --> 00:52:32,550
Sometimes.

608
00:52:33,180 --> 00:52:34,820
So you must go out on photo shoots.

609
00:52:35,520 --> 00:52:37,220
When I have a block or feel drained.

610
00:52:37,820 --> 00:52:41,020
There's hardly any information
on you out there.

611
00:52:42,190 --> 00:52:43,690
When did you return to Korea?

612
00:52:44,660 --> 00:52:46,030
Seven months ago.

613
00:52:48,030 --> 00:52:50,900
So you knew CEO Ju before that?

614
00:52:51,500 --> 00:52:53,240
Yes, back in Germany.

615
00:52:54,940 --> 00:52:56,340
So CEO Ju sought you out?

616
00:52:56,810 --> 00:52:57,810
Yes.

617
00:52:58,140 --> 00:53:00,710
After seeing my work
at the Hong Kong Art Fair.

618
00:53:01,210 --> 00:53:02,980
The Hong Kong Art Fair? When was that?

619
00:53:03,610 --> 00:53:04,610
That was two years ago.

620
00:53:05,550 --> 00:53:08,350
I missed that one.

621
00:53:10,550 --> 00:53:12,160
No wedding ring, either.

622
00:53:26,440 --> 00:53:27,440
By any chance,

623
00:53:28,100 --> 00:53:30,270
is this a painting of someone
in your family?

624
00:53:31,570 --> 00:53:32,580
Your wife?

625
00:53:34,640 --> 00:53:36,750
It's just that the feeling
I get from it...

626
00:53:37,910 --> 00:53:38,980
is so profound.

627
00:53:40,880 --> 00:53:41,880
I don't have any family.

628
00:53:43,420 --> 00:53:45,820
Single? How attractive.

629
00:53:47,990 --> 00:53:51,090
When did you start focusing on people
as your subject?

630
00:53:52,630 --> 00:53:53,730
It's been a while.

631
00:53:54,860 --> 00:53:58,600
Clients love it.
These heartfelt paintings.

632
00:54:00,900 --> 00:54:02,240
This place is perfect for a studio.

633
00:54:02,840 --> 00:54:04,470
So, are you back for good?

634
00:54:05,280 --> 00:54:06,280
I am.

635
00:54:06,540 --> 00:54:09,650
Why don't I plan a solo exhibition
for you?

636
00:54:10,710 --> 00:54:11,810
Is it because of CEO Ju?

637
00:54:13,450 --> 00:54:14,650
Mother's Gallery?

638
00:54:15,450 --> 00:54:16,450
We're in talks.

639
00:54:18,390 --> 00:54:20,520
I'll take this with me today.

640
00:54:22,390 --> 00:54:23,630
She hasn't changed a bit.

641
00:54:33,070 --> 00:54:35,170
(Paul Kim)

642
00:54:41,610 --> 00:54:42,710
(Paul Kim)

643
00:54:42,850 --> 00:54:43,880
If you find her,

644
00:54:44,610 --> 00:54:46,680
tell her...

645
00:54:47,280 --> 00:54:48,280
that her mom was so, so sorry.

646
00:54:49,090 --> 00:54:51,450
You have to find her. No matter what.

647
00:55:38,740 --> 00:55:39,940
(One Missed Call, Ran Hee)

648
00:55:44,040 --> 00:55:45,110
If you find her,

649
00:55:45,780 --> 00:55:48,010
tell her...

650
00:55:48,510 --> 00:55:49,510
that her mom was so, so sorry.

651
00:55:50,310 --> 00:55:52,720
You have to find her. No matter what.

652
00:55:52,850 --> 00:55:54,950
(Ran Hee)

653
00:55:58,120 --> 00:56:01,890
The person you have called is unavailable.
Please leave a message after the tone.

654
00:56:09,270 --> 00:56:10,300
Hyun Ran Hee.

655
00:56:11,070 --> 00:56:12,500
You've worked so hard.

656
00:56:15,740 --> 00:56:17,110
And you're still so young.

657
00:56:17,840 --> 00:56:19,310
Still in your prime.

658
00:56:21,210 --> 00:56:22,680
That girl just wouldn't listen.

659
00:56:23,380 --> 00:56:25,480
I warned her over and over
that it was dangerous.

660
00:56:26,180 --> 00:56:27,180
Is this my karma?

661
00:56:28,480 --> 00:56:29,920
Even if it is, it can't be helped.

662
00:58:37,150 --> 00:58:38,610
Hello, is this the Immigration Office?

663
00:58:39,220 --> 00:58:42,050
I'm calling to check if an acquaintance
of mine has left the country.

664
00:58:42,120 --> 00:58:44,150
I can't let you know
as it's personal information.

665
00:58:44,150 --> 00:58:45,690
Not even if I come to the office?

666
00:58:45,790 --> 00:58:46,790
It wouldn't make a difference.

667
00:58:48,190 --> 00:58:49,190
I see.

668
00:58:55,670 --> 00:58:57,100
It's 911. What's your emergency?

669
00:58:57,500 --> 00:59:00,840
- I...
- Please state your emergency.

670
00:59:01,140 --> 00:59:04,510
Hurry. Please come quick. It's my mom...

671
00:59:04,940 --> 00:59:08,710
We had a few calls.
Mr. Oh Young Sik woke up in distress.

672
00:59:08,840 --> 00:59:11,880
He's intubated,
so he couldn't express himself clearly.

673
00:59:12,110 --> 00:59:16,420
Remifentanil didn't work.
So we used Propofol, and he settled down.

674
00:59:16,750 --> 00:59:21,060
When we started Precedex for sedation,
his blood pressure dropped slightly...

675
00:59:21,390 --> 00:59:23,760
(Conference Room)

676
00:59:23,930 --> 00:59:24,930
Hello?

677
00:59:27,330 --> 00:59:32,200
(Nua General Hospital ICU gets top rating
in quality assessment!)

678
00:59:32,570 --> 00:59:37,070
We can run a check,
but it's logged in the immigration system.

679
00:59:37,810 --> 00:59:38,810
Who is it?

680
00:59:40,010 --> 00:59:41,880
- A celebrity.
- Which one?

681
00:59:42,580 --> 00:59:45,110
I'll tell you,
but you have to stick your neck out.

682
00:59:45,180 --> 00:59:47,420
If I stick my neck out and lose my job,
are you going to take responsibility?

683
00:59:47,480 --> 00:59:50,950
- You won't be fired for this.
- Get forensics to Momo's house, now!

684
00:59:53,720 --> 00:59:56,530
What's going on at Momo's?
What happened? An accident?

685
00:59:58,190 --> 01:00:00,330
Don't you know me?
You're the one who called me a pit bull.

686
01:00:02,470 --> 01:00:04,600
It looks like Momo's mother
committed suicide.

687
01:00:05,030 --> 01:00:06,170
We still have to investigate, though.

688
01:00:06,540 --> 01:00:08,470
- Why?
- How would I know?

689
01:00:09,110 --> 01:00:10,110
What about Momo?

690
01:00:10,610 --> 01:00:12,170
Apparently, she's the one who called 911.

691
01:00:13,880 --> 01:00:15,080
(Forensics)

692
01:00:19,620 --> 01:00:21,350
(Sungwoo Daily)

693
01:00:25,320 --> 01:00:26,320
(Headline)

694
01:00:26,390 --> 01:00:27,990
("Hyun Gallery CEO Hyun Ran Hee
Found Dead")

695
01:00:29,530 --> 01:00:30,660
("Hyun Gallery CEO Hyun Ran Hee
Found Dead")

696
01:00:30,660 --> 01:00:31,760
("Momo Called 911")

697
01:00:32,730 --> 01:00:35,000
(Reporter Geum Ba Ra)

698
01:00:35,200 --> 01:00:37,100
("Hyun Gallery CEO Hyun Ran Hee
Found Dead")

699
01:00:40,400 --> 01:00:42,670
(Momo discovered the body and called 911.)

700
01:00:42,740 --> 01:00:44,840
(Reporter Geum Ba Ra)

701
01:00:47,110 --> 01:00:48,940
(Reporter Geum Ba Ra)

702
01:01:15,970 --> 01:01:18,810
(Doctor Shin)

703
01:01:18,940 --> 01:01:20,610
No way. This can't be happening. How?

704
01:01:21,180 --> 01:01:23,650
- What is it, sir?
- She's relentless.

705
01:01:25,610 --> 01:01:26,620
Momo...

706
01:01:28,320 --> 01:01:30,220
James, doesn't your company sponsor Momo?

707
01:01:30,920 --> 01:01:32,490
- Yes.
- Can you introduce me?

708
01:01:32,560 --> 01:01:35,560
I didn't realize you were his best friend.
I made a complete fool of myself.

709
01:01:35,620 --> 01:01:37,660
- I'm Ha Yong Joong.
- I'm Momo.

710
01:01:37,730 --> 01:01:40,960
I can't believe it.
She got all that work done on her face,

711
01:01:41,100 --> 01:01:44,070
- and she looked so happy.
- Hyun Ran Hee is the one who died.

712
01:01:44,570 --> 01:01:46,170
Things are not what they seem.

713
01:01:46,800 --> 01:01:50,410
Just take it for what it is.
No need to overthink it.

714
01:01:50,970 --> 01:01:52,010
Loosen your tie before you go.

715
01:01:52,540 --> 01:01:55,950
I wonder where my daughter is
and if she's growing up well.

716
01:01:56,380 --> 01:02:00,050
He was the one who saw the good in me
when I felt worthless.

717
01:02:00,780 --> 01:02:04,190
- Yong Joong.
- They didn't even do CPR.
